pandoc 

  to: pptx
  output-file: example-pptx.pptx
  default-image-extension: png
  

metadata

  title: Typst Render
  subtitle: Quarto Extension
  author:
    - name: Mickaël CANOUIL, _Ph.D._
      orcid: 0000-0002-3396-4549
      url: https://mickael.canouil.fr
  extensions:
    typst-render:
      margin: 0.5em
  

(W) [typst-render] Inline Typst is not supported for PowerPoint output; inline code will be kept as-is. Pandoc cannot embed images inside text runs in PPTX slides, so block-level `{typst}` code blocks work normally but inline `{typst}` expressions cannot be rendered.

